  <h2>Risks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Interest Rates:</strong> Waste Management is highly capital-intensive and carries significant debt ($22.9B). Higher sustained interest rates could increase borrowing costs.</li>
    <li><strong>Regulatory Environment:</strong> Changes in environmental regulations, emission standards, or recycling mandates can increase compliance costs and capital expenditure requirements.</li>
    <li><strong>Economic Sensitivity:</strong> While largely defensive, industrial and commercial waste volumes can decline during severe economic contractions, impacting revenue.</li>
    <li><strong>Capital Expenditure:</strong> Maintaining and building new landfills, fleet vehicles, and renewable natural gas facilities requires heavy ongoing investment, limiting free cash flow.</li>
  </ul>

